title: Les Misérables, Vol. 2
creator: Victor Hugo
description: LibriVox recording of Les Misérables, Vol. 1, by Victor Hugo. Read by Librivox Volunteers. An ex-convict breaks parole and starts a new life as a righteous man, but is pursued by a police inspector. Along the way, the ex-convict joins a revolution, adopts a daughter, and beats people up. Hooray. (Summary by smileyman457) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; steal; romance; ex-convict; French Revolution
